  <p class="section-intro">
    Hi, my name is Nirak and I am a graduate student in Computer Science with a deep interest in the intersection of machine learning and systems.
    My research focuses on building efficient ML compilers and optimizing computation across hardware architectures.
    I am particularly drawn to compiler infrastructure like LLVM, MLIR, XLA, and TVM, 
    and how these tools can bridge the gap between high-level ML frameworks and the underlying hardware they run on.
    My long-term goal is to advance the field of ML systems through research and engineering at the compiler and architecture level.
  </p>

